  <h2>Levels 50–60: Where Poor Planning Shows</h2>
  <p>
    The final stretch exposes every shortcut taken earlier. Gold shortages, weak gear, 
    and inefficient quest paths slow players dramatically.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Complete long quest chains for strong rewards</li>
    <li>Prioritize efficient zones over nostalgia</li>
    <li>Begin preparing pre-raid gear before hitting 60</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Understanding <strong>wow classic zones by level</strong> prevents wasted travel time 
    and unnecessary grinding in this phase.
  </p>

  <h2>Levels 30–49: The Momentum Phase</h2>
  <p>
    This is where players either lock into a rhythm or burn out. 
    The key isn’t doing everything—it’s doing the right things in the right order.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Stack quests before leaving town</li>
    <li>Avoid grinding unless quests dry up</li>
    <li>Upgrade weapons frequently for faster kills</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Levels 15–29: Learning Efficiency</h2>
  <p>
    Many players struggle here due to poor zone routing and frequent deaths. 
    Commit to zone paths, manage resources carefully, and choose professions 
    that generate gold while leveling.
  </p>

  <h2>Levels 1–14: The Foundation Most Players Ignore</h2>
  <p>
    Early levels teach survival, resource management, and class mechanics. 
    Skipping class quests or early gear rewards slows long-term progress.
  </p>

  <h2>Why Leveling the Right Way Is Actually Faster</h2>
  <p>
    Speed-leveling strategies are often designed for experienced players with resources. 
    Most players level faster by dying less, saving gold, and understanding their class deeply.
  </p>

  <h2>Addons, Knowledge, and Modern Perspective</h2>
